article.description: Jenni Benningfield collected 16 points and 13 rebounds as eighth-ranked Vanderbilt shook off a sluggish first half and posted a 68-51 victory over Boston University in the season opener for both schools.
article.headline: Benningfield leads Vandy to opening win
article.linkText: No. 8 Vanderbilt overcomes poor shooting to defeat Boston
article.story:
BOSTON (Ticker) -- Jenni Benningfield collected 16 points and 13 rebounds as (No. 8 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) Vanderbilt shook off a sluggish first half and posted a 68-51 victory over Boston University in the season opener for both schools.

Benningfield's basket 16 seconds before halftime put Vanderbilt (1-0) ahead for good at 23-22. The Commodores shot just 35 percent (8-of-23) in the first half.

Vanderbilt used an 8-1 run, fueled by six points from Benningfield, to establish its first double-digit lead at 40-30 with 13:39 left.

Rachael Vanderwal's 3-pointer pulled Boston University (0-1) within 45-38 with 10:29 to play. Ashley Earley and Ashley McElhiney each had four points in a 10-0 run that extended the Commodores' lead to 55-38 with just over eight minutes to go.

Hillary Hager scored 14 points, Chantelle Anderson added 13 and Tia Battle 11 as Vanderbilt shot 68 percent (15-of-22) in the second half. McElhiney added eight points and six assists.

Katie Terhune scored 20 points and Marisa Moseley added nine for the Terriers, who shot just under 30 percent (18-of-61) and were outrebounded, 42-30.

Boston University drew the second-largest crowd in school history at 829.
